## Second-pass complete

**Draft updated:** `src/blog/people/drafts/Tobey-Maguire.md`

I read the fresh-eyes review, verified every factual claim by web search, then made a substantive edit pass. The biggest changes:

**Filled the marriage gap (the review's #1 issue).** Added a new section on Jennifer Meyer (married 2007, separated 2016, divorce finalized 2020, two kids). It's not just a biographical patch — I used it to put the draft's own thesis under pressure: friendship is the alliance a Six *can* hold; marriage asks for a dependence he can't secure in advance. It closes on "The pack absorbed her" (he converted an ex-wife into the one form of alliance he trusts).

**Added two on-theme film beats the draft was leaving on the table:**
- *The Great Gatsby* (2013) in the DiCaprio section — the two teenage friends finally on screen together, Maguire cast as Nick Carraway, the watchful outsider. A near-perfect 6w5 payoff.
- *Pawn Sacrifice* (2014, Bobby Fischer) as a second pillar in the "walked away" section alongside Babylon — a Six playing chess's most famous paranoiac right as he exited stardom.

**Added the Ruderman Ponzi clawback** (won $300k+, settled $80k denying wrongdoing) to the poker material — the controlled table turning on him, exactly the fear he games against.

**Trimmed the echoes:** cut one of the four verbatim "two temperatures" restatements (the diagnosis-section one), and fixed the "uncertainty engineered out" repeat in the close (now "a floor that cannot drop," which callbacks the "floor is not guaranteed" motif).

**Protected what was working:** the empathy turn, the "concede the point" paragraph, and the inner-thought block, all untouched. Left the Spider-Man 2 Rabbit Hole reference as-is — it's already a compressed clause, not a duplicated scene.

**Still open for an editor:** the "turns cold" section is now the longest in the piece after the Ruderman add. It reads as earning its length to me, but an editor could trim the Bloom equipment detail if they disagree.

Sources for the facts I verified: [Nicki Swift – Meyer divorce](https://www.nickiswift.com/271202/the-real-reason-tobey-maguire-is-getting-divorced/), [Hollywood Reporter – $80K poker settlement](https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/business/business-news/tobey-maguire-pays-80000-settle-266579/), [Forbes – Ruderman lawsuit](https://www.forbes.com/sites/chrisbarth/2011/06/22/tobey-maguire-billionaire-alec-gores-being-sued-for-poker-winnings-from-jailed-ponzi-schemer/), [Wikipedia – Pawn Sacrifice](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pawn_Sacrifice), [Wikipedia – The Great Gatsby (2013)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Great_Gatsby_(2013_film)).
